ng environment | polymerization reported; exact yields not extracted | Yanagawa et al. 1984 *Origins of Life* |\n\n## Source-count statement and unresolved coverage gaps\n\n- **Total source rows gathered in s6:** 392\n- **Deduplicated source count:** 342\n- **Broader multi-angle search coverage:** 4000+ sources touched prior to validation filtering; the report body keeps the validated s6 subset and related content unchanged.\n- **Unresolved coverage gaps:**\n  - quantitative yields/selectivities are mostly absent from the validated carried-forward artifact\n  - hydrothermal T/P/pH details are incomplete except for the preserved **200-275 \u00b0C** note\n  - no carried-forward direct clay-catalyzed de novo glycine synthesis row\n  - cyanosulfidic direct glycine production remains unresolved in the validated network\n  - iron-sulfur de novo synthesis remains contradicted by negative evidence\n\n## References\n\nAponte, J. C., et al. (2020). *ACS Earth and Space Chemistry*.\n\nAubrey, A. D., et al. (2009). *Origins of Life and Evolution of Biospheres*.\n\nAfrin, R., et al. (2018). *International Journal of Molecular Sciences*.\n\nAlonso, J. L., et al. (2018). *Astrophysical Journal*.\n\nBelloche, A., et al. (2008). *Astronomy & Astrophysics*.\n\nBernstein, M. P., Sandford, S. A., Allamandola, L. J., Chang, S., and Scharberg, M. A. (1995). *Astrophysical Journal*.\n\nBernstein, M. P., et al. (2002). *Nature*.\n\nBizzarri, B. M., et al. (2021). *International Journal of Molecular Sciences*.\n\nBl\u00f6chl, E., Keller, M., W\u00e4chtersh\u00e4user, G., and Stetter, K. O. (1992). *Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences USA*.\n\nBujd\u00e1k, J., Eder, A., Yongyai, Y., Fayb\u00edkov\u00e1, K., and Rode, B. M. (1995). *Journal of Inorganic Biochemistry*.\n\nBujd\u00e1k, J., Son, H. L., and Rode, B. M. (1996). *Journal of Inorganic Biochemistry*.\n\nChimiak, L., et al. (2024). *Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences USA*.\n\nCleaves, H. J. (2008). *Precambria